	<ul>
		<li><strong>Do not post any copyrighted texts here!</strong>
			Please note that any content submitted to MusicBrainz will be
			made available to the public under <a href="/about/licenses.html">
			open licenses</a>.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Wiki Format:</strong> Annotations support a limited set of wiki
			formatting options:

			<table style="margin-left: 30px">
				<tr class="top">
					<td style="padding-right: 40px">Emphasis:</td>
					<td>
						''italics''; '''bold'''; '''''bold italics'''''; ---- horizontal rule</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="top">
					<td>Headings:</td>
					<td>
						=&nbsp;Title&nbsp;1&nbsp;=; ==&nbsp;Title&nbsp;2&nbsp;==; ===&nbsp;Title&nbsp;3&nbsp;===</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="top">
					<td>Lists:</td>
					<td>
						tab or 4 spaces and: * bullets; 1., a., A., i., I. numbered items; spaces alone indent</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="top">
					<td>Links:</td>
					<td>
						url; [url]; [url|label]</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="top">
					<td>Misc:</td>
					<td>
						Because square brackets [] are used to create hyperlinks, you have to
						use the encoded html equivalents (<code>&amp;#91;</code> for [") and (<code>&amp;#93;</code> for ])
						if you want them not be converted into hyperlinks. Example: If you want
						to use [unknown] in the annotation, you'll have to write
						<code>&amp;#91;unknown&amp;#93;</code>
						that it will appear the way you intended it to show.
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>

			<div style="padding: 5px; margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 30px; border: 1px dotted red;">
				<strong>Please use the wiki formatting sparingly!</strong>
				The wiki formatting is intended to give a some
				flexibility for annotations and should not interfere
				with the rest of the page layout.
			</div>
		</li>
	</ul>

